org.team1540.rooster.drive.pipeline

Interface Output<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of the output.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Consumer<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CTREOutput
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface Output<T>
extends Consumer<T>
    Extension of a Consumer adding an additional composition method. Output can be used exactly like Consumer (and library functions should not take Outputs as method parameters, instead using Consumer). However, library functions pertaining to drive pipelines should return an Output where they would normally return a Consumer.
